Visualize Data

Load libraries

We defined the input_file parameter in the YAML header. This is documented in the Rmarkdown user guide.

Generate plot

Now, well read-in the data and visualize it using ggplot2.

iris_df = read_csv(params$input_file)
## Warning: Missing column names filled in: 'X1' [1]
ggplot(iris_df, aes(x=sepal_width, y=sepal_length, color=species)) + 
              geom_point()
